# Shell tooling (`bin/`)

Repo dispatch scripts (`bin/dispatch-kimi`, `bin/wf-log`, `bin/wf-extract-segment`) are **zsh**. Match existing style mechanically when editing.

## Zsh

- Shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env zsh`
- Arrays are 1-indexed; use glob qualifiers and extended parameter expansion

## Bash (if used elsewhere)

- Shebang: `#!/usr/bin/env bash`
- `set -euo pipefail`
- Quote variables: `"${var}"`; use `local` in functions
- Errors to stderr: `echo "Error: ..." >&2`

## Dispatch changes

When changing Kimi dispatch or external-agent behavior:

- Read **`docs/external-agent-protocol.md`** (authoritative for execution mechanics)
- Plans handed to external implementers must reference that protocol (see **`CLAUDE.md`**)

Do not embed Cursor-specific instructions in dispatch scripts.
